[
    {
        "content": "<p>We had a talk by Neeman yesterday. Formalizing the completion of a category with respect to a metric seems like a reasonable target. Heck triangulated categories are in reasonably in scope now. For background, see Neeman’s <a href=\"https://arxiv.org/abs/1901.01453\">notes</a></p>",
        "id": 432727395,
        "sender_full_name": "Matthew Ballard",
        "timestamp": 1712847916
    },
    {
        "content": "<blockquote>\n<p>We’ve said it before: in this free world of ours there is no law prohibiting a mathematician from making up a long sequence of absurd-looking definitions.</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 432728467,
        "sender_full_name": "Matthew Ballard",
        "timestamp": 1712848210
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>It sounds cool (and actually kind of related to some discussions we had in LTE) but are there any applications you have in mind?</p>",
        "id": 432728865,
        "sender_full_name": "Adam Topaz",
        "timestamp": 1712848324
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>GAGA?</p>",
        "id": 432729021,
        "sender_full_name": "Matthew Ballard",
        "timestamp": 1712848373
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>how does GAGA fit into the picture?</p>",
        "id": 432729097,
        "sender_full_name": "Adam Topaz",
        "timestamp": 1712848391
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><a href=\"https://arxiv.org/abs/1804.01976\">https://arxiv.org/abs/1804.01976</a></p>",
        "id": 432729147,
        "sender_full_name": "Matthew Ballard",
        "timestamp": 1712848406
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Super cute</p>",
        "id": 432729166,
        "sender_full_name": "Matthew Ballard",
        "timestamp": 1712848415
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Of course it would blow up the scope by orders of magnitude to just get these as categories</p>",
        "id": 432729338,
        "sender_full_name": "Matthew Ballard",
        "timestamp": 1712848462
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Note that my PhD student <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"252627\">@Jujian Zhang</span> is actively thinking about how to approach GAGA right now.</p>",
        "id": 432729745,
        "sender_full_name": "Kevin Buzzard",
        "timestamp": 1712848596
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Locally-ringed G-spaces is G-spaces in the sense of rigid geometry?</p>",
        "id": 432729780,
        "sender_full_name": "Adam Topaz",
        "timestamp": 1712848606
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I think those are subset but confess to knowing nothing more than what is in the paper</p>",
        "id": 432730241,
        "sender_full_name": "Matthew Ballard",
        "timestamp": 1712848729
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Also I don't really see where metrics on categories comes into play in that GAGA paper...</p>",
        "id": 432730367,
        "sender_full_name": "Adam Topaz",
        "timestamp": 1712848763
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Metrics let you prove that certain functors out of <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msup><mi>D</mi><mi>b</mi></msup><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">coh</mi><mo>⁡</mo><mi>X</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">D^b(\\operatorname{coh} X)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1.0991em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.02778em;\">D</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.8491em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">b</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mop\"><span class=\"mord mathrm\">coh</span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span> are representable. Now you apply this to the functor </p>\n<p><span class=\"katex-display\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" display=\"block\"><semantics><mrow><mi>E</mi><mo>↦</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Hom</mi><mo>⁡</mo><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"script\">A</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>E</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mi>F</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">E \\mapsto \\operatorname{Hom}(\\mathcal A(E),F)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6943em;vertical-align:-0.011em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.05764em;\">E</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">↦</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mop\"><span class=\"mord mathrm\">Hom</span></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathcal\">A</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.05764em;\">E</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">F</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span></span></p>\n<p>where <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"script\">A</mi><mo>:</mo><msup><mi>D</mi><mi>b</mi></msup><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">coh</mi><mo>⁡</mo><mi>X</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo>→</mo><msup><mi>D</mi><mi>b</mi></msup><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">coh</mi><mo>⁡</mo><msup><mi>X</mi><mrow><mi>a</mi><mi>n</mi></mrow></msup><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathcal A : D^b( \\operatorname{coh} X) \\to D^b( \\operatorname{coh} X^{an})</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathcal\">A</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">:</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1.0991em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.02778em;\">D</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.8491em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">b</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mop\"><span class=\"mord mathrm\">coh</span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">→</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1.0991em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.02778em;\">D</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.8491em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">b</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mop\"><span class=\"mord mathrm\">coh</span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.6644em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">an</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span> is an analytification functor</p>",
        "id": 432731299,
        "sender_full_name": "Matthew Ballard",
        "timestamp": 1712848993
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>This produces an adjoint</p>",
        "id": 432731380,
        "sender_full_name": "Matthew Ballard",
        "timestamp": 1712849024
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>scrap that... it should be more similar to something like a uniform structure on <code>Arrow C</code>.</p>",
